with b as (
  select
    bet_id,
    player_id,
    game_id,
    placed_at,                         -- was bet_time
    stake::double precision   as stake,
    odds::double precision    as odds,
    status,
    actual_win::double precision as actual_win
  from stg_bets
)

select
  bet_id,
  player_id,
  game_id,
  cast(placed_at as date) as bet_date, -- was bet_time
  placed_at,
  stake,
  odds,
  status,
  actual_win
from b

with src as (
  select
    placed_at,                               -- unified timestamp from stg_bets
    game_id,
    player_id,
    stake::double precision       as stake,
    actual_win::double precision  as actual_win,
    lower(status)                 as status
  from stg_bets
)
select
  date_trunc('day', placed_at)                                 as day,
  game_id,
  count(*)                                                      as bets,
  sum(case when status = 'won'  then 1 else 0 end)             as wins,
  sum(case when status = 'lost' then 1 else 0 end)             as losses,
  sum(stake)                                                   as handle,
  sum(coalesce(stake,0) - coalesce(actual_win,0))              as ggr,
  avg(case when status='won' then 1.0 else 0.0 end)            as win_rate
from src
group by 1,2
order by 1,2

-- Top 5 players by total bet in last 30 days per game_type (joins games)
with last_30 as (
  select b.player_id, g.game_type, sum(b.stake) total_bet
  from public.bets b
  join public.games g using(game_id)
  where b.bet_time >= (current_date - interval '30 day')
  group by 1,2
),
ranked as (
  select *, row_number() over(partition by game_type order by total_bet desc) rn
  from last_30
)
select * from ranked where rn <= 5 order by game_type, total_bet desc

with legacy as (

    bet_id::text                 as bet_id,
    player_id::integer           as player_id,
    game_id::integer             as game_id,

    stake::double precision      as stake,
    odds::double precision       as odds,
    lower(status::text)          as status,
    actual_win::double precision as actual_win
  from public.bets
),
stream as (
  select
    bet_id,
    player_id,
    game_id,
    bet_time::timestamp          as placed_at,
    stake,
    odds,
    lower(status)                as status,
    actual_win
  from public.bets_stream
)
select * from legacy
union all
select * from stream
